---
// Voice A/B overview — issue #67 (part of epic #65).
// Not linked from the live site's nav; excluded from robots.txt.
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const title = "Voice A/B — Overview";
const description =
  "Three tone variants of the landing page and framework index, for side-by-side review. Not part of the live site.";
---

<SiteLayout title={title} description={description} isArticle={true}>
  <h1>Voice A/B: three arms</h1>
  <p>
    Two representative pages &mdash; the landing page and the
    <code>/framework/</code> index &mdash; rendered in three tone variants,
    so the voice question (issue #67, part of epic #65) can be decided once
    and then applied mechanically across the rest of the site. These pages
    sit outside the live site's navigation and are not linked from it.
  </p>

  <h2>Arm A &mdash; John's voice</h2>
  <p>
    Prose adapted from John's staged-facade bundle
    (<code>context/raw/FAND_staged_facade/index.html</code> and
    <code>framework.html</code>) &mdash; the Ship-of-State framing,
    Welth/the Enumeration, the 10-K analogy, in full, on both pages.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/voice-ab/a/">Landing</a></li>
    <li><a href="/voice-ab/a/framework/">Framework index</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Arm B &mdash; descriptive-neutral</h2>
  <p>
    The site's current register &mdash; the same register used today on
    <code>/about/</code>, <code>/methodology/</code>, and
    <code>/evidence/</code>.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/voice-ab/b/">Landing</a></li>
    <li><a href="/voice-ab/b/framework/">Framework index</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Arm C &mdash; hybrid</h2>
  <p>
    John's voice on the landing page, a persuasion surface; descriptive-neutral
    on the framework index, a reference/scannable surface. Each page reuses
    the exact copy from Arm A or Arm B respectively &mdash; the hybrid is a
    choice of <em>which page gets which voice</em>, not a blended tone
    within a page.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/voice-ab/c/">Landing</a> (John's voice)</li>
    <li><a href="/voice-ab/c/framework/">Framework index</a> (descriptive-neutral)</li>
  </ul>
</SiteLayout>
